{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Cocoa Development Tips"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gain tips from seasoned framework engineers about how to get the most out of your Cocoa development efforts.  For example, find out how you can get perfect hashing behavior from NSDictionary with a simple API.  From best practices to lesser known APIs, there is something for everyone to learn."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-236-Cocoa-Development-Tips","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/236\/","overridingTitle":"Read Transcript"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-236-cocoa-development-tips"]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-210-Whats-New-in-Core-Data","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-215-Whats-New-in-Accessibility"]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}],"alt":null},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-215-Whats-New-in-Accessibility":{"abstract":[{"text":"Discover what’s new in accessibility in iOS, watchOS, macOS, and tvOS.  Learn how to audit an App for accessibility, and take advantage of new assistive features.  Topics include how to best customize how Voice Over describes an App UI to the user, how to enhance the accessibility user experience with new features like Drag and Drop, and how to take advantage of sophisticated accessibility APIs to solve common issues.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-215-Whats-New-in-Accessibility","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"What’s New in Accessibility","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-215-whats-new-in-accessibility"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-212-whats-new-in-foundation","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Whether you’re building apps for iOS, macOS, watchOS, or tvOS, a lot of the functionality you get from Apple’s SDKs comes from the Foundation framework. Join the Foundation engineering team to hear about the improvements they’ve been working on. Learn how significant changes to key paths can help make your code safer with strong type checking in Swift. Hear all about how the new archiving API can help you safely convert your native Swift types to and from external formats like JSON.  Gain insights into performance enhancements that will help make your app even more efficient.","type":"text"}],"title":"What’s New in Foundation","type":"topic"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/236/":{"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/236\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/236\/","checksum":null},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-210-Whats-New-in-Core-Data":{"title":"What’s New in Core Data","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-210-Whats-New-in-Core-Data","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Join the Core Data engineering team and learn about the new features in Core Data.  See how you can easily and automatically include your data in Spotlight to allow users to find content even if it’s stored in Core Data.  Learn about new options for indexing your data, and hear the details on a new feature for tracking changes over time.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-210-whats-new-in-core-data","type":"topic"}}}